==English==
===Etymology===
First attested circa [[w:18th century|18th century]], from [[Spanish]].
===Proverb===
'''don't [[teach]] your [[grandmother]] to [[suck]] [[egg]]s'''
# don't tell an [[expert]] how to do things
#: ''Teach-your-grandmother-to-suck-eggs—ducks' eggs!'' &mdash; [[w:Bog-Myrtle and Peat|Bog-Myrtle and Peat]] by [[w:Samuel Rutherford Crockett|Samuel Rutherford Crockett]]

====Translations====
*Russian: [[яйца курицу не учат]] (jájtsa kúritsu ne účat)
*Finnish: [[Älä opeta isääsi kusemaan]] (Don't tell your father how to pee)
*French: [[Les oisons veulent mener les ois paitre]] (The goslings want to drive the geese to pasture)
*Greek: [[Έλα παππού μου να σου δείξω τ' αμπελοχώραφά σου]] (Come grandfather, I 'll show you your vines)
